╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  HELIX TRAINER — Exercise 1.1: Basic Motion                     ║
║  Category: Movement              Difficulty: ★☆☆ Fundamental    ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

COMMANDS TO LEARN
─────────────────
  h     Move left
  j     Move down
  k     Move up
  l     Move right

MNEMONIC: h is leftmost, l is rightmost, j hangs down, k points up

INSTRUCTIONS
────────────
  Each line below contains a word marked with brackets [like this].
  Your goal: delete ONLY the bracketed word (including brackets).

  Steps for each line:
  1. Use h/j/k/l to move your cursor onto the [ character
  2. Press  v  to enter select mode
  3. Use  l  to extend your selection to include the ]
  4. Press  d  to delete

  Do NOT use w, b, f, or any other motion — only h, j, k, l.

────────────────────────── PRACTICE ──────────────────────────────

The quick [brown] fox jumps over the lazy dog.
She sells [sea] shells by the seashore.
How much [wood] would a woodchuck chuck?
Pack my [box] with five dozen liquor jugs.

────────────────────────── EXPECTED ──────────────────────────────

The quick  fox jumps over the lazy dog.
She sells  shells by the seashore.
How much  would a woodchuck chuck?
Pack my  with five dozen liquor jugs.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HINTS (read only if stuck):
  Hint 1: Position cursor on [, press v, then l repeatedly until
          ] is included in the selection, then d.
  Hint 2: Remember: in Helix, motions CREATE selections. So just
          moving with h/j/k/l already selects the character under
          the cursor. v extends it as you move.
